-- Padres Acquire Miguel Tejada, Cash From Orioles for Minor-Leaguer Pelzer
-- Nancy Kercheval
-- 2010-07-30T04:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-30/padres-acquire-miguel-tejada-cash-from-orioles-for-minor-leaguer-pelzer.html

          
          
             The San Diego Padres acquired six-
time All-Star infielder  Miguel Tejada  and cash from the
Baltimore Orioles in exchange for minor-league pitcher Wynn
Pelzer, General Manager  Jed Hoyer  said.  
 Tejada, 36, is hitting .269 with 16 doubles, 7 home runs,
39 runs batted in and 40 runs scored in 97 games this season.
Originally signed by the Oakland Athletics in 1993, he has
hit .288 with 292 home runs and 1,224 RBIs over 14 Major League
Baseball seasons.  
 Pelzer, 24, has appeared in 22 games this year for the
Padres Double-A affiliate in San Antonio. He was signed as a
ninth-round selection in the 2007 First-Year Player Draft.  
